<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Recorded from southern Brazil and neighbouring Argentina growing in deciduous forest margins and scrub.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">ARGENTINA. Misiones</emphasis>
: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Iguazú">Iguazu</normalizedToken>
, Wanda, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.A. Keller &amp; H.F. Romero</emphasis>
13252 (CTES, OXF); Montecarlo, Col. Guatambo, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.A. Keller</emphasis>
4038 (CTES).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BRAZIL. Rio Grande do Sul</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P.P.A. Ferreira &amp; J. Durigon</emphasis>
705 (ICN, INPA); 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco de Paula, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Seynam</emphasis>
10020 (MBM). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Santa Catarina</emphasis>
: Descanso. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R.M. Klein</emphasis>
5119 (HBR) fide Ferreira et al. (2013: 32).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes</emphasis>
. This species is distinguished by its small outer sepal and very lax, branched inflorescence and glabrous corolla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The placement of this species is uncertain.</paragraph>
